1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,263
JavaScript functions are a fundamental building block for writing reusable pieces of code

2
00:00:06,237 --> 00:00:11,463
They allow developers to write a block of code once and reuse it whenever needed throughout the program

3
00:00:12,475 --> 00:00:16,562
This ability promotes DRY  Don't Repeat Yourself  principles

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,788
making codebase more maintainable and organized

5
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:21,312
Furthermore

6
00:00:21,475 --> 00:00:24,050
functions are first-class citizens in JavaScript

7
00:00:24,262 --> 00:00:26,238
meaning they can be assigned to variables

8
00:00:26,562 --> 00:00:28,688
passed as arguments to other functions

9
00:00:28,962 --> 00:00:30,825
and returned from other functions

10
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:33,450
providing great flexibility in coding

